---
/**
 * ai-infrastructure/0001 · Figure 2 — Module 1, "Each hop: one job, one risk".
 * Verbatim from the source HTML (figure + svg + figcaption incl. footnote <sup>).
 * Uses marker-end="url(#arw)" — the #arw def is emitted once by Fig1.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A vertical breakdown of each hop in the stack with its single job and its dominant risk."
    >
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Each hop: one job, one risk</text
        >

        <!-- hop rows -->
        <rect x="40" y="34" width="170" height="30" rx="5" fill="#f6eef7" stroke="#b5179e"></rect>
        <text x="125" y="53" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Embedding model</text
        >
        <text x="226" y="53" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >job: text &rarr; vector &middot; risk: model/version drift</text
        >

        <rect x="40" y="70" width="170" height="30" rx="5" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="125" y="89" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Vector DB (ANN)</text
        >
        <text x="226" y="89" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >job: find near neighbors &middot; risk: recall vs latency</text
        >

        <rect x="40" y="106" width="170" height="30" rx="5" fill="#fbf3e6" stroke="#8a5a0f"></rect>
        <text x="125" y="125" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#8a5a0f"
            >Reranker</text
        >
        <text x="226" y="125" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >job: precision on top-K &middot; risk: can't recover misses</text
        >

        <rect
            x="40"
            y="142"
            width="170"
            height="30"
            rx="5"
            fill="#eef2f7"
            stroke="#1f3a5a"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="125" y="161" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >Model gateway</text
        >
        <text x="226" y="161" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >job: auth/route/cache/limit &middot; risk: chokepoint</text
        >

        <rect
            x="40"
            y="178"
            width="170"
            height="30"
            rx="5"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="125" y="197" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Inference server</text
        >
        <text x="226" y="197" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >job: forward pass &middot; risk: KV memory caps batch</text
        >

        <!-- spine connector -->
        <line x1="125" y1="64" x2="125" y2="70" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="125" y1="100" x2="125" y2="106" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="125" y1="136" x2="125" y2="142" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="125" y1="172" x2="125" y2="178" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>

        <text x="320" y="232" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-style="italic" fill="#6b675f"
            >First two stages select WHAT to send; the last two govern HOW it's served. Different
            SLOs, different teams.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Two halves: a <em>retrieval</em> half (embedding, vector DB, reranker) that decides <b
            >what</b
        >
        goes into the prompt, and a <em>serving</em> half (gateway, inference) that decides <b
            >how</b
        >
        the answer is produced. This track is the ops deep dive on both.<sup
            ><a href="#s1" id="r1c">1</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
